args:
Mitsuhide sleeps all day, Hanabusa is a great
dancer with a weak stomach, and Nobunaga is
a Wyrmclan leader with no respect for custom.
Despite being bewildered by their new allies'
eccentricities, the Prince's group sets off with
them to find Ebisu and recover the stolen gifts.
Mitsuhide! Where aaare yoou?!\nHmm. I was SURE they went this way.
There are many fiends in these parts.\nPerhaps she made a detour in order\nto avoid an unpleasant encounter.
Nah, those guys would never run\nfrom a fight. It's way easier to just\ncut the fiend into little gooey bits.
Yer boss sounds like she's got\na bit of the berserker in her.
Actually, the berserker in question is...\nWell, you'll understand when you meet.\nLet's just focus on finding them for now!
So then! It's afternoon. Clear weather.\nWhat would Mitsuhide do here...?
In a pursuit situation, I imagine she would\nattempt to gain as much ground on her\ntarget as possible while the sun shone.
Nope! She'll be taking a nap.
Might I offer you some tea?\nIt's nothing special, but I pray you\nfind it palatable regardless.
Yes, it's me! And YOU are here lazing\nabout when you're supposed to be chasing\ndown the thieving kitty dragon!
What are you doing having some leisurely\ntea party in a place like this—AND without\neven inviting me, might I add?!
This is no tea party—it's a war briefing.\nWe're plotting how best to crush our\nenemies before us like a great wheel.
Say, Chitose? Who are these people?
They came from the Halidom to help us.\nI shared a few teensy details of our\npredicament in order to secure their aid.
Explain what you mean when you say\n＂a few teensy details.＂
I admitted everything! I spilled the beans!\nI sang like a canary! I squealed! I ratted!\nI'M NOT GOOD AT THIS, OKAY?!
But now they're gonna help us catch\nthe fortune thief, so THAT'S good.
Er, right. Anyway, it's nice to meet you.\nI'm {player_name}.
Ah. Then I suppose we should\nintroduce ourselves as well.
Of course. My name is Hanabusa.
I've come to perform a traditional\nHinomotoan dance for all of you.
It will be—URK! Ooo, my stomach...
No, stress always makes me... Ah...\nN-never mind. Happens all the time.\nDaikokuten, why don't you go ahead?
I am Daikokuten, pactwyrm to Mitsuhide\nof the Twelve Wyrmclans.
Is ＂pactwyrm＂ what the leaders of the\nTwelve Wyrmclans call the dragons\nwith whom they share a soulpact?
Indeed, for ours is a most divine bond.
Well, I'm pleased you're here, but also\na little surprised since Ieyasu's dragon,\nMarishiten, didn't come when he visited.
Marishiten cares for nothing but battle.\nI, however, wanted to see this.
After all, it may present a chance to sink\nmy teeth into something divine.
Oh ho! When I happen upon the divine,\nI cannot resist taking a little nibble!
Um, okay. So if Hanabusa is the dancer,\nand Daikokuten is Mitsuhide's dragon...
Then you must be Lady Mitsuhide,\nleader of the Mouse Clan!
I am indeed a Wyrmclan leader!
But mine is the Horse Clan...\nand my name is Nobunaga!
I believed the Wyrmclans to travel\nindependently. Why would the leaders\nof two different clans come in this case?
Traditionally, such a thing is true.\nBut I refuse to be bound by tradition!
It is my dream to unify this world,\nso I have come to learn what I can\nof foreign lands!
I suppose I can understand that.\nBut in that case, where is Mitsuhide?
You will find the leader of the\nMouse Clan...THERE!
I knew it. ...Master! Wake up already!
You're a dignitary in a foreign land,\nand you've gotta act like it!
Come on, Master, pull it together.\nAt least introduce yourself to our guests!
*yaaawn* Mmrph. Name's Mitsuhide.\nI lead the Mouse Clan.
THIS is the Mouse Clan leader?
Pleasure and so forth. Yada yada.\nYou can take it from here. G'night.
Master, no! You're the one who's\nsupposed to be responsible for this!\nYou can't go back to sleep!
Okay, this is not at ALL what I was\nexpecting to happen today.
What happened to ＂serious, solemn,\nand capable,＂ Cleo? WHAT HAPPENED?!
So this is how you make tea in Hinomoto?\nIt tastes a tad unripe, but there is a rather\nsignificant depth to it as well.
Its very astringency is what makes it taste\nso good when paired with sweets.
Now THAT is something I must try.
Um, excuse me? I hate to interrupt,\nbut why are you two having tea and\nrelaxing? What about Ebisu?!

Dealing with all of their idiosyncrasies
has proven to be too much for me.
Instead, I have decided to simply relax
and ＂go with the flow,＂ as it were.
Look, I get the urge to do that. Trust me.\nBut can we at least discuss the situation\nwhile you drink your tea?
There's so much we don't understand.\nLike who is this Ebisu, and why would\nhe steal all the gifts?
Who he is or what he wants matters not.\nOur way forward is clear...
We must cleave the miscreant in twain\nand reclaim the purloined presents!\nTo arms! To aaaaarms! RRRAAAAGH!
Okay, that one sleeps all day,\nand this one is clearly insane.\nAin't we got a middle ground?

Right then! Maybe we should all just
stop doing...whatever we're doing,
chase down Ebisu, and take back
all of the stolen merchandise.
Sounds like a plan to me—though I ain't\nsure how I feel about cleavin' someone\nin twain on an empty stomach.
Then we should probably get moving.\nLet's start by waking Mitsuhide and—
Yep. Gotta get the gifts back.
Because if we DON'T get 'em back,\nLady Amaterasu'll be reeeal angry.
I brought you along because you're\nsupposed to be the heir to a great\nschool of dance.
But if we can't spread good fortune,\nyou can't perform your dance.
And you know what happens then, right?
*shudder* Y-yes, my lady! I assure you,\nI will fight to the best of my ability!
Good. Because I expect no less.\n...You too, Daikokuten.
Yes, you. I know this Ebisu character is\nan old acquaintance of yours, so stop\nmoping and go do something about it!
Right! Glad we had this talk.\nYou guys all go shake a leg while\nI catch a few more Zs and—
Oh no, Mitsuhide. You're coming, too.\nLet's punish that bad kitty together.
Fine, fine! Just let go before you\ntear my damn ear off already!
I don't have a great feeling about this,\nbut let's go find this Ebisu!
